Reasoning: 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is the most likely category as the paper deals with the reconstruction of a modal logic in terms of linear logic. 
- cs.LG (Computational Geometry) is also likely as the paper mentions the Geometry of Interaction Machine semantics. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is relevant as the paper discusses the Curry-Howard correspondence and lambda-calculus. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is possible as modal logic is used in AI applications. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is less likely but still possible as the paper deals with staged computation.
